#: ../../user-guide.md:1974
msgid "❓ FAQ"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:1976
msgid "General"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:1978
msgid ""
"**Q: Is pyMM free?** A: Yes! pyMM is open-source software licensed under "
"MIT. Free to use, modify, and distribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:1981
msgid ""
"**Q: Does pyMM require internet connection?** A: Only for initial plugin "
"downloads and updates. Once installed, pyMM works completely offline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:1984
#, python-format
msgid ""
"**Q: Can I run pyMM on macOS or Linux?** A: Yes! pyMM runs on Windows "
"10+, Windows 11, Ubuntu 20.04+, Debian 11+, and macOS 11+. Configuration "
"directories follow platform standards (XDG Base Directory on Linux, "
"~/Library on macOS, %APPDATA% on Windows)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:1987
msgid ""
"**Q: How much storage does pyMM need?** A: ~200 MB for application. "
"Plugins vary (12 MB - 450 MB each). Projects depend on your media."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:1990
msgid "Projects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:1992
msgid ""
"**Q: Can I share projects with others?** A: Yes! Archive projects and "
"share the archive file. Recipients extract and open in their pyMM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:1995
msgid ""
"**Q: What happens if I move pyMM to another drive?** A: pyMM is fully "
"portable. Move the entire `D:\\pyMM` folder to any drive and run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:1998
msgid ""
"**Q: Can I have projects on multiple drives?** A: Yes! Configure project "
"location per-project. Mix local, external, and network drives."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:2001
msgid ""
"**Q: How do I backup projects?** A: Use built-in archive feature or copy "
"project folders manually. Git integration provides version history."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:2004
msgid "Plugins"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:2006
msgid ""
"**Q: Are plugins safe?** A: All official plugins are verified and "
"downloaded from trusted sources (GitHub, official websites)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:2009
msgid ""
"**Q: Can I use my existing DigiKam database?** A: Yes! Configure DigiKam "
"plugin to point to your existing database location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:2012
msgid ""
"**Q: Why are some plugins so large?** A: Plugins include full "
"applications (DigiKam, FFmpeg) for portability. No system installation "
"needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:2015
msgid ""
"**Q: Can I create custom plugins?** A: Yes! See [Plugin Development Guide"
"](plugin-development.md) for instructions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:2018
msgid "Performance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:2020
msgid ""
"**Q: Why is pyMM slow on my USB drive?** A: USB 2.0 drives are slow. Use "
"USB 3.0+ or move application to faster storage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:2023
msgid ""
"**Q: Can I use SSD for application and HDD for media?** A: Yes! Install "
"pyMM on SSD (`C:\\pyMM`), configure project location on HDD "
"(`D:\\pyMM.Projects`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-guide.md:2026
msgid ""
"**Q: How much RAM does pyMM use?** A: Typically 200-500 MB idle, up to "
"2-4 GB when processing large projects."
msgstr ""

